thread.title: X Factor Boys: Here's how Twitter reacted as Nick Grimshaw chose his final three
thread.title_full: X Factor Boys: Here's how Twitter reacted as Nick Grimshaw chose his final three

title: X Factor Boys: Here's how Twitter reacted as Nick Grimshaw chose his final three
text:
— My Name's Joy (@musthaveloved) October 25, 2015 
Fans of the show certainly gave the 19-year-old their stamp of approval. 
Although a few eagle-eyed people spotted that Sean Miley Moore’s photo appeared on screen when Che’s name was announced. Awkward much? Che has just got through but Sean's pic is up? Weird that Sean is then 3rd picked? #xfactor #blunder pic.twitter.com/CmE1LB4OcH 
— ML Hudson (@ml_hudson) October 25, 2015 Awkward moment when Che's name was announced and they put a photo of Sean on the screens before he was even through… #XFactor 
— Angharad Yronwy (@Gingereed) October 25, 2015 
Nick’s final choice was Seann Miley Moore who promised us more heels and broken nails. Seann Miley Moore (Syco / ITV) 
Fans were mostly happy. 
— Jessie Booth (@JessieBooth_1) October 25, 2015 #xfactor @Sean Miley Moore has to win xfactor! 
— Jo Marle de Cera (@JEMDC) October 25, 2015 I'm just glad Sean got through tbh #XFactor 
Although, people can’t help but wonder heels played a part in his success. Sean only got through because he's a guy in heels. #XFactor #Controversial 
— Laura Davison (@LauraaDavisonn) October 25, 2015 
However, a lot of people were kind of hoping Josh Daniel would be in the final three. Josh Daniel (ITV)
